name: Alien Probe
description: Cannon that revs up, slides to the side, and stacks down 1 to the side of the rev power

name: All-Y
description: Cannon that can change y level by increments of 1

name: Anti Gravity / Anti Grav / AG
description: Cannon that has a small y exposure, making it shoot up on walls

name: Anti Patch / AP
description: Cannon that uses an extra power to tunnel through blocks placed behind the shot

name: Array Cannon
description: Cannon that uses webs to shoot entities and stop them mid air with different exposures

name: Auto Adjust
description: Cannon that can adjust automatically

name: Bone-Bust
description: Cannon that shoots the nuke downwards into obsidian below a previously created airgap, making a wider hole in the wall

name: Booster
description: TNT used to boost entities forwards

name: Cannon Box / Cbox
description: Box used to protect a cannon

name: Counter Cannon / Counter
description: Cannon used to destroy cannons setup on your base

name: Cubic Cannon / Cubic
description: Cannon using x, y and z exposure differences smaller than 1

name: Efficient AP / Eff-AP
description: Cannon that has a late nuke, making it possible to tunnel through watered blocks on the second shot without an extra power

name: Efficient Nuke / Eff-Nuke
description: Nuking using multiple gameticks of nuke and a nuke hammer

name: Entity
description: A dynamic, moving object, that can be affected by gravity

name: Exposure
description: The efficiency of the explosion of a TNT entity towards another entity

name: Force Cannon
description: A cannon used to raid someone else's base

name: Fusion
description: A cannon (or part of a cannon) that can shoot through a 1x1 for a certain amount of chunks

name: Hammer
description: TNT that explodes for the purpose of stacking sand, the amount of sand it can stack is relative to the amount of velocity it gives to the sand

name: Hybrid
description: A cannon that stacks sand and has a scatter

name: Late Nuke
description: A cannon with a nuke going off later than usual (subjective)

name: Leftshooter / Lefty
description: A cannon that hits a wall, and then uses another power to shoot entities to the left

name: Low Y Cubic / LYC
description: A cubic with a y level lower than usual, giving better exposures

name: L-Stacker
description: A cannon that triangles up, then gets shot down and starts going forward at y255 bypassing all walls in front of it

name: Midair
description: A cannon that does not require a backboard to stack sand

name: Midair Left-shooter / Midair Lefty
description: A leftshooter that does not require a backboard for the lefty power

name: Midair Splitter
description: Splitter tnt used to separate entities and give entities different velocities  in mid air, mainly used  for 1 power fusions

name: Multi-TNT
description: Dispenser that dispenses multiple TNT entities at once

name: One Shot Regen Busting / OSRB
description: A cannon that is able to destroy the lava sources of a regen in one shot

name: OOE Stacking
description: Stacking by rendering sand before hammer and shooting it with 1 power

name: Order Of Entities / OOE
description: The order in which entities affect eachother

name: Overstacker / OS
description: A cannon that stacks above barrel height, commonly done by using upwards hammer swing

name: Pseudo Nuke
description: Rendering TNT in between layers of sand, making multiple holes in the wall

name: Push Nuke
description: A cannon that pushes the nuke and nuke hammer into the wall in front of it, making a wider hole

name: Render Queueing
description: Using falling sand rendered in between entities to separate them

name: Reverse Hybrid / Rev Hybrid
description: Cannon that shoots hammer and sand up using a reverse power, then stacks down and scatters

name: Reverse Nuke / Rev Nuke
description: Cannon that shoots hammer and sand up using a reverse power, then stacks down and nukes

name: Reverse Scatter / Rev
description: Cannon that shoots scatter up using a reverse power, then scatters

name: Right Shooter / Righty
description: A cannon that hits a wall, and then uses another power to shoot entities to the right

name: Slabbust
description: TNT that gets tunneled down using hammer as tunneling power, destroying any slabs below it

name: Splitter Fusion
description: Stacking using splitter TNT for a more efficient hammer ratio

name: Scatter
description: TNT that explodes for the purpose of destroying watered obsidian

name: Tunneling
description: Effect created by rendering 2 TNT entities differently in the same gametick, instantly destroying dry blocks in front of it

name: Tunneler
description: Cannon that tunnels

name: U-Fusion
description: Cannon that uses multiple barrels to shoot entities

name: Up Down Nuke
description: Cannon that shoots an upnuke and a downnuke into a previously created sandstack, nuking up, down and making a wider hole in the wall

name: Velocity
description: The speed at which an entity is traveling in a certain gametick

name: Velocity Udirectional Anti Gravity / VUAG
description: Cannon that gives the entities a y velocity to get really small y exposures

name: Wall Remover
description: Cannon that Reverse Nukes and triangles the nuke, creating horizontal lines in the wall

name: Webbust
description: Method of tunneling that involves TNT exploding in mid air

name: Worm
description: Cannon that “stacks” sand horizontally by method of sliding
